        <div class="section">
            <p class="sectitle"><b>About Our Food</b></p>
            <img src="images/meal.jpg" id="steakimg" alt="Cooked Steak Image">
            <p id="aoftext">
                The Slavic Stove serves up hearty and flavorful Eastern European cuisine.
                The menu features classic dishes like pierogies, borscht, and schnitzel, as well as more unique offerings like stuffed cabbage rolls and potato pancakes.
                Pierogies are a favorite, with fillings like cheese and potato or sweet fruit and cheese.
                The Slavic Stove celebrates the rich flavors and traditions of Eastern Europe, with every dish a taste of home.
                At The Slavic Stove, the chefs take great care in using high-quality, locally sourced ingredients to ensure that every dish is both delicious and healthy.
                The restaurant is committed to supporting local farmers and suppliers, and many of the vegetables, meats, and dairy products used in the kitchen come from nearby farms and producers.
                The chefs also use traditional cooking techniques that preserve the nutrients and flavors of the ingredients, resulting in dishes that are not only satisfying but also packed with nutrients.
                For example, the borscht soup is made with beets, which are a great source of fiber, potassium, and vitamin C, while the stuffed cabbage rolls are filled with a blend of ground pork and healthy vegetables like carrots and onions.
                The Slavic Stove's commitment to using local ingredients and healthy cooking techniques has won over health-conscious diners who are looking for tasty and nutritious options when dining out.
                The restaurant's menu is a testament to the belief that healthy eating and delicious food can go hand in hand, making it a popular destination for foodies and health enthusiasts alike.

            </p>
